q = Queue()

# Enqueue items
q.enqueue(1)
q.enqueue(2)
q.enqueue(3)

# Dequeue items
print(q.dequeue())  # prints 1
print(q.dequeue())  # prints 2
print(q.dequeue())  # prints 3

# Check if queue is empty
print(q.is_empty())  # prints True
```

This implementation uses two stacks, `stack_newest_on_top` and `stack_oldest_on_top`, to implement a queue. The `enqueue` operation is simply a `push` operation on `stack_newest_on_top`. The `dequeue` operation involves popping items from `stack_newest_on_top` and pushing them onto `stack_oldest_on_top` until `stack_oldest_on_top` is not empty, and then popping from `stack_oldest_on_top` to get the front item.
